# Baseline Regression (Mean Predictor)

This module mirrors the structure of your `logistic_regression` project but implements a **baseline regression** for `ldl`: a model that always predicts the training mean of the target and is evaluated with **MSE**.

## How to run

```bash
# 1) Evaluate baseline with 10-fold CV and save artefacts
python -m baseline_regression.run --folds 10 --save-predictions

# 2) Produce constant predictions for a CSV (any columns)
python -m baseline_regression.inference  # writes manual_inference.csv using a dummy row
# or
python - <<'PY'
from baseline_regression.inference import main
main(input_csv="path/to/your_rows.csv", output_csv="preds.csv")
PY
```

## Outputs (under `baseline_regression/results/mean_baseline_regression/`)
- `cv_metrics.csv` — MSE per fold.
- `predictions.csv` — in-sample `actual` vs `predicted` (if `--save-predictions`).
- `model.joblib` — contains the learned global mean for `ldl`.
- `summary.json` — quick summary with mean/std MSE.
